<title>SWEDEN: Ericsson signs accord with UK's  Thorn.</title>
<headline>Ericsson signs accord with UK's  Thorn.</headline>
<dateline>STOCKHOLM 1996-09-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Swedish telecom LM Ericsson AB said on Thursday it signed an agreement with British security company  Thorn Security Ltd for 5,000 radio modems.</p>
<p>It gave no value for the order.</p>
<p>Ericsson said in a statement the 5,000 Mobidem M2050 radio modems would be used in Thorn's new Siteguard Smart Signaling alarm services.</p>
<p>&quot;The new services will be available to Thorn's thousands of customers throughout the U.K. in mid-September,&quot; Ericsson said.</p>
<p>The statement said Thorn Secuity recently joined the U.S. based Tyco group.</p>
<p>-- Stockholm newsroom +46-8-700 1003</p>
